<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9804> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9804" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/16> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 223" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1359> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1359" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed without a Master of Horse to revise the roll of the Senate, a task which he promptly completed, and immediately abdicated (Liv. 23.22.10-23.8; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 119, 444f.; Plut. Fab. 9; cf. Lyd. Magg. 1.37; see Mommsen, Str. 1.626, note 3; 2.148, 159, note 2; Bandel, 133-135)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1312> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1312" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These men, defined by Livy as maiores natu, were sent to Carthage with Rome's ultimatum (Liv. 21.18.1, cf. 21.19.6, and 20.9; Dio fr. 55.10; Zon. 8.22; cf. Polyb. 3.20.6 and 9, and 33.1-4, and 40.2; Frontin. Str. 1.11.4; Sil. Ital. 2.1-390; App. Ib. 13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1308> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1308" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy clearly believes that the leader of this embassy was Q. Fabius Maximus, but Dio and Zonaras call him M. Fabius, who would then be the senior ex-Censor M. Fabius Buteo (Cos. 245, Cens. 241). Willems suggests (2.503, note 3) that {Gr} in Dio is a corruption of {Gr}, but the absence of the name in Polybius and the silence regarding the event in the Elogium, Plutarch's life of Fabius Maximus, and the Auct. Vir. Ill. tend to favor Buteo. The choice remains uncertain. See Münzer, RE s. v. \"Fabius,\" no. 116, col. 116f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1200> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1200" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (C. Aurelius C. f. C. n. Co[tta]), Degrassi 42f., 117, 438f.; cf. Jerome Chr. ad ann. 244, p. 132 Helm; and on Fabius, Liv. 23.22.10; Fabius' name must be supplied here in Fast. Cap. since all the other possible places are definitely known." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1189> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1189" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Flor. 1.18.30, on Buteo; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; see Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f. Florus (1.18.30-32) speaks of a victory over the Punic fleet at Aegimurus, followed by storm and shipwreck, Zonaras (8.16) of the continued changes of command." .
